						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/Commodities/Livestock/Related-developments/A-new-option-for-managing-climate-risk-in-Africa" title="A new option for managing climate risk in Africa" alt="link">A new option for managing climate risk in Africa</a></h2>

	
					<p>Thousands of herders in arid areas of northern Kenya will soon be able to buy livestock insurance, based on a first-of-its-kind program in Africa. The program was announced on January 22 in northern Kenya’s Marsabit District by the International Livestock Research Institute (ILRI), microfinance pioneer Equity Bank and African insurance provider UAP Insurance Ltd. Insuring the livestock of pastoralist families has long been considered impossible because of the difficulty of verifying deaths of animals, which move over vast tracts of land in search of food. ILRI and its partners have overcome this impediment by combining the use of satellite images of vegetation with monthly surveys of livestock deaths to pinpoint the level of forage reduction that will cause animals to die. (Source: CGIAR, 22 January 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/02/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/Commodities/Livestock/Related-developments/A-new-option-for-managing-climate-risk-in-Africa">Read more...</a>
</div>
