						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/Commodities/Livestock/Related-developments/Deadly-cattle-plague-on-the-brink-of-eradication" title="Deadly cattle plague on the brink of eradication" alt="link">Deadly cattle plague on the brink of eradication</a></h2>

	
					<p>Rinderpest, one of the deadliest cattle diseases, is set to become the first animal disease to be eradicated from the planet. The FAO announced November 30th that it expects, along with the World Organisation for Animal Health and other partners, to declare the disease wiped out in the next 18 months. Cattle plague, as rinderpest is also known, has killed millions of cows and other hoofed animals. It is caused by a virus and spreads through contact, and by water and food contaminated with the dung of infected animals. The disease can kill all infected animals in an outbreak, losing farmers money and food. (Source: SciDev.net, December 9, 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">21/12/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/Commodities/Livestock/Related-developments/Deadly-cattle-plague-on-the-brink-of-eradication">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
