					<p>The twelfth Brussels Development Briefing was held on 1st July 2009 and dealt with “The Role of Livestock for ACP countries: challenges and opportunities ahead”. This Briefing discussed key issues on livestock for ACP countries and reviewed the role of livestock for ACP economies and the drivers of change. Different people amongst whom Mr. Carlos Seré, the Director General of the International Livestock Research Institute (ILRI) and Dr. Francis Asiedu from the Caribbean Agriculture Research and Development Institute (CARDI) gave their view on the topic in a video-message. (Brussels Development Briefings, 13 July 2009)</p>
